    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "·         A curriculum was designed as a guide to 40-week discussion series targeting at increasing the capacity of married couples to understand and prevent Intimate Partner Violence (IPV) in their community.\r\n\r\n·         Four trainings to the 72 facilitators to conduct 40 weekly discussions with 72 groups based in three districts. In addition, a Training of Trainers (TOT) on community mobilization was organized for 12 selected facilitators who organized a series of cascading training for other facilitators.\r\n\r\nTwo workshops with social and religious leaders organized to provide a forum for the leaders to reflect on their own position and capacity to respond to violence against women."
      },
      "ne": null
